@startuml
left to right direction
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor Student
actor Lecturer
actor Admin

rectangle EduSecure {
  usecase "Authenticate" as UC1
  usecase "View Visible Spaces and Assignments" as UC2
  usecase "Submit Assignment for Visible Space" as UC3
  usecase "Review Submission Integrity Metadata" as UC4
  usecase "View Own Grades for Visible Submission" as UC5
  usecase "Create / Update Grades" as UC6
  usecase "Create Managed User Accounts" as UC8
  usecase "Create Assignments for Owned Spaces" as UC9
  usecase "Manage Owned Spaces" as UC10
}

Student --> UC1
Student --> UC2
Student --> UC3
Student --> UC5

Lecturer --> UC1
Lecturer --> UC2
Lecturer --> UC4
Lecturer --> UC6
Lecturer --> UC8 : student accounts only
Lecturer --> UC9
Lecturer --> UC10

Admin --> UC1
Admin --> UC4 : oversight
Admin --> UC6 : oversight
Admin --> UC8 : student + lecturer accounts
Admin --> UC9 : oversight
Admin --> UC10 : oversight

UC3 ..> UC4 : <<creates metadata for>>
UC6 ..> UC4 : <<requires verified submission>>

note bottom of EduSecure
Assignments are linked to spaces rather than standalone courses.
Student submission and student self-service grade access
are limited to assignments that remain visible through
the student's current space memberships.

Audit logging is implemented internally for user creation,
space changes, submissions, and grades, but there is no
actor-facing audit review API/UI in the current codebase.

Managed user creation is intentionally limited:
- ADMIN can create STUDENT and LECTURER accounts
- LECTURER can create STUDENT accounts only
end note
@enduml

